===Etymology 1===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} tentatively suggests comparisons with {{och-l|遹|to follow}}, as well as an areal word family represented by {{cog|km|ទ័ព|t=army}}, based on superficial semantics and a reconstruction of the Old Chinese as {{m|och||*duus}}.

However, based on reconstructions by Zhengzhang and Baxter-Sagart, compare instead {{cog|my|လုတ်|t=mouthful of food}}, which is a much stronger phonetic match and semantically reasonable (as a "grouped unit").

